<subSubSection id="92942902D98658019A7881DBB2C37999" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="6EF615511C83880A7A7D49C55AC4CD87" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A647704E254490035D2CAB97647A5E44" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
In Macau, adults are active from late spring to mid-summer and range in total length 15-18 mm and 6-7.5 mm in maximum width. Individuals are readily attracted to artificial lights at night, but are also active during the day while crawling and mating on dead tree surfaces. In Hong Kong, 
<taxonomicName id="977EF9DCD7EA1E17ED4AF487C8B3F94B" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Mangifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mangifera indica" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis id="72B3E57C592158CEB9A9A5B2727DC20F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Mangifera indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="682FA7FFA4CB1AAA04FBBEE4F91AD30E" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fabaceae" genus="Derris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Derris" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7C4A36E9E42C9A00F289D43DEAF50DAC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Derris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. have been reported as food plants for the larvae of this species (
<bibRefCitation id="9AE562D7643381040141B6BDAE2E1138" author="Yiu, V" journalOrPublisher="Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B161" refString="Yiu, V, 2009. Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1. Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" title="Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1." year="2009">Yiu 2009</bibRefCitation>
). Other host plants include 
<taxonomicName id="2FB3C99E1209C440C3239F9411BD518B" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fabaceae" genus="Derris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Derris trifoliata" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="trifoliata">
<emphasis id="B126BAFEB1C5962D7138CC54A488F07F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Derris trifoliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="87ED373A39082D0A21F964FDC72B4985" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Hevea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Hevea brasiliensis" order="Geraniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="190A1A875733F5209473ED3D4B769122" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Hevea brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3C64AB0596D58962124CD94E31014DEA" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Mangifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mangifera indica" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis id="5613B973C20AF5B841F3A4CD5E263E60" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Mangifera indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DE1C5D52E1477B3D3A6B7B908F2FF8F2" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Quercus" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="184A17FD5306EC1AC1257938D4265710" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., 
<taxonomicName id="C23910D611ED64F0D6D5BFD46E3026EB" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Dipterocarpaceae" genus="Shorea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Shorea" order="Guttiferales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="93D54CE08399E36653D21767E2FBE96E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Shorea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. and 
<emphasis id="F54C86AA7D2E7D63F8F1EC578CD41929" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Terminalia</emphasis>
sp. (
<bibRefCitation id="3E347C1C0CE2CFEC68ED097FC72CA825" author="Lin, M-Y" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B89" refString="Lin, M-Y, Yang, X-K, 2019. Catalogue of Chinese Coleoptera, Vol. IX. Chrysomeloidea: Vesperidae, Disteniidae, Cerambycidae. Science Press, Beijing" title="Catalogue of Chinese Coleoptera, Vol. IX. Chrysomeloidea: Vesperidae, Disteniidae, Cerambycidae." year="2019">Lin and Yang 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
